at.nineyards.anyline.modules.ocr

Interface AnylineOcrBaseListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ModuleResultListener
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AnylineOcrListener

    public interface AnylineOcrBaseListener
extends ModuleResultListener
    A base result listener for the Anyline OCR module with all none UI relevant callbacks.
    Since:
    3.4.2

    • Method Detail

      • onReport

        void onReport(String identifier,
              Object value)

        Called with interesting values, that arise during processing.

        Some possibly reported values:

        • $brightness - the brightness of the center region of the cutout as a float value (NumUtil.asFloat(value))
        • $confidence - the confidence, an Integer value between 0 and 100 (NumUtil.asInt(value))
        • $thresholdedImage - the current image transformed into black and white (the base image used for OCR)

        Parameters:
        identifier - the identifier of the reported value
        value - the value

      • onAbortRun

        void onAbortRun(AnylineOcrError code,
                String message)
        Is called when the processing is aborted for the current image before reaching return. (If not text is found or confidence is to low, etc.)
        Parameters:
        code - the reason code
        message - the reason in textual (english) form

      • onResult

        void onResult(AnylineOcrResult result)
        Called if a result is found.
        Parameters:
        result - a result object containing the image and the result
